snippet.textDisplay:
SE Dons Player Ratings #1 (Kenningwell PPC Cup Quarter Final)

Big G (8/10) - Clean Sheet can't ask for anything more
Azz (8/10) - didn't really see much of him today, but I'll give him a 8 for keeping the clean sheet
Jazz (9/10) - best centre back at the club, another top performance today
DR (8/10) - I feel like DR doesn't get enough attention, most underrated player at the club, another solid performance
Mal (8/10) - didn't see much of the full backs today, but again Mal and Azz put in a shift and that's all we ask for
Lefty (6/10) - came off early, didn't really see much of him today
RP7 (8/10) another solid performance from Ryan today, one of the most hardworking players at the Dons
Montel (9/10) - man of the match today, dictated the midfield today against a good Kenningwell side
K - Runna (8/10) - another good shift for Runna, another underrated player at the Dons
Zak Ansah (9/10) - this guy can't stop scoring, my player of the season so far this season
J - Boogie (9/10) - Debut goal, looks a good talent

Subs
Nathan Palmer (5/10) - came on late, didn't see much of him
Oz (5/10) - need to see more of Oz, the guy is a baller
Ginge (1/10) - didn't play, but gave the lads a good warm up 1 star for you
Nad (5/10) - did he even come on?
King (7/10) - did well when he came on

Side line (7/10) - not the best of atmospheres today, but did pick up near the end, good banter and Chants with the Kenningwell boys near the end.
